The paper discusses a methodology for designing approximate accelerators using libraries of approximate circuits. This falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) as it deals with the design of hardware systems. The methodology also involves machine learning techniques for fast design space exploration, which could fall under the categories of embedded systems (cs.ET), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), and emerging technologies (cs.EM).
